#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Dhajaggasutta"
msgstr "3. The Banner’s Crest"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.472"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn11.3:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn11.3:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn11.3:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn11.3:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:2.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi."
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, a battle was fought between the gods and the "
"demons."

msgctxt "sn11.3:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.219"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:3.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace, mārisā, devānaṃ saṅgāmagatānaṃ uppajjeyya bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā "
"lomahaṃso vā, mameva tasmiṃ samaye dhajaggaṃ ullokeyyātha."
msgstr ""
"‘Good sirs, when the gods are fighting, if you get scared or terrified, just "
"look up at my banner’s crest."

msgctxt "sn11.3:3.2"
msgid ""
"Mamañhi vo dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā "
"lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissati."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:4.1"
msgid ""
"No ce me dhajaggaṃ ullokeyyātha, atha pajāpatissa devarājassa dhajaggaṃ "
"ullokeyyātha."
msgstr ""
"If you can’t see my banner’s crest, then look up at the banner’s crest of "
"Pajāpati, king of gods."

msgctxt "sn11.3:4.2"
msgid ""
"Pajāpatissa hi vo devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā "
"chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissati."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:5.1"
msgid ""
"No ce pajāpatissa devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokeyyātha, atha varuṇassa "
"devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokeyyātha."
msgstr ""
"If you can’t see his banner’s crest, then look up at the banner’s crest of "
"Varuṇa, king of gods."

msgctxt "sn11.3:5.2"
msgid ""
"Varuṇassa hi vo devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā "
"chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissati."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:6.1"
msgid ""
"No ce varuṇassa devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokeyyātha, atha īsānassa "
"devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokeyyātha."
msgstr ""
"If you can’t see his banner’s crest, then look up at the banner’s crest of "
"Īsāna, king of gods."

msgctxt "sn11.3:6.2"
msgid ""
"Īsānassa hi vo devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā "
"chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissatī’ti."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.473"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: nopi pahīyetha → no pahīyetha (mr)
msgctxt "sn11.3:7.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sakkassa vā devānamindassa dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ, "
"pajāpatissa vā devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ, varuṇassa vā devarājassa "
"dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ, īsānassa vā devarājassa dhajaggaṃ ullokayataṃ yaṃ "
"bhavissati bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyethāpi nopi "
"pahīyetha."
msgstr ""
"However, when they look up at those banner’s crests their fear and terror "
"might go away or it might not."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:8.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn11.3:8.2"
msgid ""
"Sakko hi, bhikkhave, devānamindo avītarāgo avītadoso avītamoho bhīru chambhī "
"utrāsī palāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Because Sakka is not free of greed, hate, and delusion. He gets fearful, "
"scared, terrified, and runs away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:9.1"
msgid "Ahañca kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "But, mendicants, I say this:"

msgctxt "sn11.3:9.2"
msgid ""
"‘sace tumhākaṃ, bhikkhave, araññagatānaṃ vā rukkhamūlagatānaṃ vā "
"suññāgāragatānaṃ vā uppajjeyya bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā, "
"mameva tasmiṃ samaye anussareyyātha:"
msgstr ""
"If you’ve gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut "
"and you get scared or terrified, just recollect me:"

msgctxt "sn11.3:9.3"
msgid ""
"“itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "sn11.3:9.4"
msgid ""
"Mamañhi vo, bhikkhave, anussarataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā "
"lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissati."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.220"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:10.1"
msgid "No ce maṃ anussareyyātha, atha dhammaṃ anussareyyātha:"
msgstr "If you can’t recollect me, then recollect the teaching:"

msgctxt "sn11.3:10.2"
msgid ""
"“svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko "
"paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

msgctxt "sn11.3:10.3"
msgid ""
"Dhammañhi vo, bhikkhave, anussarataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ "
"vā lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissati."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.474"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:11.1"
msgid "No ce dhammaṃ anussareyyātha, atha saṅghaṃ anussareyyātha:"
msgstr "If you can’t recollect the teaching, then recollect the Saṅgha:"

msgctxt "sn11.3:11.2"
msgid ""
"“suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho "
"ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā esa bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho, āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ "
"puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the "
"eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is "
"worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of "
"a teacher’s offering, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the "
"supreme field of merit for the world.’"

msgctxt "sn11.3:11.3"
msgid ""
"Saṅghañhi vo, bhikkhave, anussarataṃ yaṃ bhavissati bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ "
"vā lomahaṃso vā, so pahīyissati."
msgstr "Then your fear and terror will go away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:12.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn11.3:12.2"
msgid ""
"Tathāgato hi, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vītarāgo vītadoso vītamoho "
"abhīru acchambhī anutrāsī apalāyī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"Because the Realized One is free of greed, hate, and delusion. He does not "
"get fearful, scared, terrified, or run away.”"

msgctxt "sn11.3:12.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn11.3:12.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:13.1"
msgid "“Araññe rukkhamūle vā,"
msgstr "“In the wilderness, at a tree’s root,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:13.2"
msgid "suññāgāreva bhikkhavo;"
msgstr "or an empty hut, O mendicants,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Anussaretha → anussareyyātha (mr)
msgctxt "sn11.3:13.3"
msgid "Anussaretha sambuddhaṃ,"
msgstr "recollect the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:13.4"
msgid "bhayaṃ tumhāka no siyā."
msgstr "and no fear will come to you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:14.1"
msgid "No ce buddhaṃ sareyyātha,"
msgstr "If you can’t recollect the Buddha—"

# I’m not sure if BB’s “best in the world” is a translation or an oversight. In any case, I am not aware of a variant lokasettha.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:14.2"
msgid "lokajeṭṭhaṃ narāsabhaṃ;"
msgstr "the eldest in the world, the bull of a man—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:14.3"
msgid "Atha dhammaṃ sareyyātha,"
msgstr "then recollect the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:14.4"
msgid "niyyānikaṃ sudesitaṃ."
msgstr "emancipating, well taught."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:15.1"
msgid "No ce dhammaṃ sareyyātha,"
msgstr "If you can’t recollect the teaching—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:15.2"
msgid "niyyānikaṃ sudesitaṃ;"
msgstr "emancipating, well taught—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:15.3"
msgid "Atha saṅghaṃ sareyyātha,"
msgstr "then recollect the Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:15.4"
msgid "puññakkhettaṃ anuttaraṃ."
msgstr "the supreme field of merit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.475"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.3:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ buddhaṃ sarantānaṃ,"
msgstr "Thus recollecting the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:16.2"
msgid "Dhammaṃ saṅghañca bhikkhavo;"
msgstr "the teaching, and the Saṅgha, mendicants,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:16.3"
msgid "Bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā,"
msgstr "fear and terror"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.3:16.4"
msgid "Lomahaṃso na hessatī”ti."
msgstr "and goosebumps will be no more.”"
